<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: The Quest for Exotic Ingredients (help needed)</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Xarn">Xarn</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:22 p.m. 16/8/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: The Quest for Exotic Ingredients (help needed)<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/quest.cgi?read=652" TARGET=_self>Re: The Quest for Exotic Ingredients (help needed)</A> (Xarn)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Well this quest is an amazingly easy thing to do IF you've got the time to wander in 4 different cities, It will ultimately get you a glowing stein ( int +10, dex+5, hp +10, sv vs disease +20). The problem is that the last leg of quest once you get the 4 ingredients recquire an enchanter lvl 20 who can cast benevolence and illusion ogre or DE. Anyway, the item you get from the barkeep once you give him the 4 ing. is some money and a 'compendium' which is a no drop lore item. Make sure you got an enchanter who you can trust to give these items to barkeep, otherwise the quest is all for nothing except the 3-4pp you get, which is byfar nothing compared to the glowing stein which can be sold for 300-500pp depending on the servers.

<P>Once your 'mule' enchanter gets the 'compendium' make the trek to ogguk to a barkeep called 'clurg' I think thats his name. Make sure your enchanter has illusion ogre or DE casted and also benevolence, (can use a lvl 12 DE enchanter who has never killed any ogres casting 'alliance') before he wanders there to clurg, have him activate the quest, (clurg is actually the start point of quest where he asks you to retrieve the 'compendium' for him from gregor the barkeep in freeport) Once your mule gives him the compendium, he gets the glowing stein.
<P>Now to actually answer your question, kill the fish that swims in the lake at the 'temple of life'( doing so will give you a negative faction hit with the guards in temple, will KOS), but the corpse will have the koalindl fish which is lore item.
<P>The tonic is attained by buying 'innoruk's kiss of death' for 2 silver in erudin at 'Hawk's Tavern' in the courtyard near the library, then take that to (can't remeber her name but she is on top floor of the library with a few other people), giving that to her will get you the erudin's tonic.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
